<p itemprop="description">Problem management involves identifying and addressing the root causes of incidents and service disruptions to prevent their recurrence and improve service quality and stability.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the difference between incidents and problems, and recognise the importance of root cause analysis in improving service quality.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can investigate problems using structured approaches, contribute to root cause analysis, and implement solutions to prevent problem recurrence.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can manage complex problem investigation processes, coordinate problem resolution activities, and establish proactive problem identification methods.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can design enterprise problem management frameworks, establish problem management culture, and drive continuous service improvement through systematic problem resolution.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

